HEADWORD: Encauma
<hw>En*cau"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr. <?/
mark caused by burning, fr. <?/. See <er>Encaustic</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An ulcer in the eye, upon the cornea, which
